Reasoning: The paper deals with tracking and estimating channel gains in wireless communication systems, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a novel channel-gain monitoring scheme that leverages recent advances in compressive sensing (cs.SI) and interference processing in wireless communication (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the overhead of channel gain monitoring, which is related to distributed systems (cs.DS).
